# Bloomberg Mock Demo

This repo demos building on Bloomberg market data without a real terminal.

- `examples/`, `tester-app/` — upstream InteropIO `@glue42/bbg-market-data` samples (reference only).
- `demo/` — the live demo: a Next.js + TypeScript app.
  - `src/lib/mock-bbg/` — mock of `@glue42/bbg-market-data` (factory, request types, synthetic feed). Swap the import for the real package to talk to a live terminal.
  - `src/lib/server/` — market engine, SQLite layer (`better-sqlite3`), reporting job (`node-cron`).
  - `src/app/api/**` — backend routes (`securities`, `stream`, `history`, `reports`, `reports/run`, `movers`).

## Conventions

- The dashboard UI is intentionally built live during demos; the baseline state is **backend only**.
- To reset between demos, run `demo/refresh-demo.sh`.
- This is mock/synthetic data — never present it as real market data.
